<div class="unit-details">
    <div class="content-box">
        <h2 class="content-title"><i class="fa-solid fa-user-secret"></i> MAIN TASK – The John Doe Investigation
        </h2>

        <p>You will explore a set of images from a fictional person called John Doe. All of these images were
            found publicly online. Your job is to work out what you can learn about him from the clues in the
            pictures.</p>

        <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

        <h3>1. What You Need to Find</h3>
        <p>Using the 15 dossier images, find at least <strong>10 pieces of information</strong> about John.</p>
        <p>Your list must include:</p>
        <ul class="custom-list">
            <li>John’s name</li>
            <li>John’s date of birth (day + month)</li>
            <li>The city John lives in</li>
        </ul>
        <p>After that, you can find any other clues you discover.</p>

        <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

        <h3>2. How to Record Your Findings</h3>
        <p>Create a table in your exercise book:</p>

        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
            <thead>
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa; border-bottom: 2px solid #e0e0e0;">
                    <th style="padding: 10px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;">Image Number</th>
                    <th style="padding: 10px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;">What information
                        does this image reveal?</th>
                    <th style="padding: 10px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;">Should this be
                        public or private? Why?</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; color: #888;">(e.g. 1)</td>
                    <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;"></td>
                    <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;"></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>Fill in the table as you look at the images. You can choose any details you spot — big or small. Some
            examples might include hobbies, routine, places he visits, things he likes, family information, or
            anything else you can reasonably work out from what you see.</p>

        <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

        <h3>3. Look Carefully</h3>
        <ul class="custom-list">
            <li>Not every clue is obvious.</li>
            <li>Some images may reveal more than one piece of information.</li>
            <li>Think about how different details link together.</li>
            <li>Ask yourself: “What does this tell me about John?” and “Would this be safe to share?”</li>
        </ul>

        <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

        <h3>4. Reflection (Write This Under Your Table)</h3>

        <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-color);">A. What picture can you build of
                John Doe?</h4>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Write 4–5 bullet points describing what kind of person John appears
                to be based only on the information you found.</p>

            <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-color);">B. What should have stayed private?
            </h4>
            <p>Choose three items from your table that you think should not have been shared publicly. For each
                one, write one sentence explaining the risk or concern.</p>
        </div>

        <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

        <h3>5. Partner Discussion</h3>
        <p>Discuss your findings with the person next to you. Share one thing you discovered that you didn’t
            expect.</p>

        <div
            style="background: #eef2f7; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 2rem 0; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-color);">
            <h4 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-color);"><i
                    class="fa-solid fa-graduation-cap"></i> By the End of This Task, You Should Be Able To…</h4>
            <ul class="custom-list" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                <li>Explain the difference between public and private information online</li>
                <li>Recognise how small pieces of data can build a picture of someone</li>
                <li>Understand why sharing too much online can be risky</li>
                <li>Describe what responsible digital behaviour looks like</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

